{"title_page": "Halmeu", "text_new": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = commune\n|county                 = Satu Mare\n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Satu Mare County\n|name=Halmeu\n|other_name=Halmi\n|image_map              = Halmeu jud Satu Mare.png\n|coordinates = {{coord|47|58|N|23|1|E|region:RO|display=it}}\n}}\n'''Halmeu''' ({{lang-hu|Halmi}}, {{IPA-hu|\u02c8h\u0252lmi|pron}}; {{lang-yi|\u05d4\u05d0\u05b7\u05b7\u05dc\u05de\u05d9\u05df}}) is a [[Communes of Romania|commune]] of 4,845 inhabitants situated in [[Satu Mare County]], [[Romania]]. It is composed of five villages:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! In [[Romanian language|Romanian]] \n! In [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]]\n|-\n| B\u0103be\u0219ti\n| Kisb\u00e1bony\n|-\n| Dobol\u021b\n| Dabolc\n|-\n| Halmeu\n| Halmi\n|-\n| Halmeu-Vii\n| Halmihegy\n|-\n| Mesteac\u0103n\n| Ny\u00edrestanya\n|}\n\nUntil [[World War II]], the village was home to a Jewish community, which numbered 479 souls in 1877.<ref>[http://data.jewishgen.org/wconnect/wc.dll?jg~jgsys~shtetm~-1161123 JewishGen locality page for Halmeu]</ref> The commune included two other villages until 2005, when they were split off to form [[Porumbe\u0219ti, Satu Mare|Porumbe\u015fti]] Commune.\n\n==Demographics==\n\nIn 1910, 97.6% reported Hungarian as their primary language. The religious make-up was 1196 Calvinists (34.6%), 1061 Jewish (30.7%) and 613 Roman Catholic (17.7%).\n\nEthnic groups (2011 census):<ref>[http://www.recensamantromania.ro/rezultate-2/ Tab8. Popula\u0163ia stabil\u0103 dup\u0103 etnie \u2013 jude\u0163e, municipii, ora\u015fe, comune], 2011 census results, [[National Institute of Statistics (Romania)|Institutul Na\u021bional de Statistic\u0103]], accessed 10 March 2020.</ref> \n*[[Romanians]]: 57%\n*[[Hungarians in Romania|Hungarians]]: 36%\n*[[Romani people in Romania|Roma]]: 3%\n\n57% had [[Romanian language|Romanian]] as first language, and 39% [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]].<ref>[http://www.recensamantromania.ro/rezultate-2/ Tab10. Popula\u0163ia stabil\u0103 dup\u0103 limba matern\u0103 \u2013 jude\u0163e, municipii, ora\u015fe, comune], 2011 census results, [[National Institute of Statistics (Romania)|Institutul Na\u021bional de Statistic\u0103]], accessed 10 March 2020.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n* [http://simania.co.il/bookdetails.php?item_id=481430 Memorial book to the Communities of Halmin-Turt] (in Hebrew)\n\n{{LocalitiesSatuMare}}\n\n[[Category:Communes in Satu Mare County]]\n\n\n{{SatuMare-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = commune\n|county                 = Satu Mare\n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Satu Mare County\n|name=Halmeu\n|other_name=Halmi\n|image_map=\n|coordinates = {{coord|47|58|N|23|1|E|region:RO|display=it}}\n}}\n'''Halmeu''' ({{lang-hu|Halmi}}, {{IPA-hu|\u02c8h\u0252lmi|pron}}; {{lang-yi|\u05d4\u05d0\u05b7\u05b7\u05dc\u05de\u05d9\u05df}}) is a [[Communes of Romania|commune]] of 4,845 inhabitants situated in [[Satu Mare County]], [[Romania]]. It is composed of five villages:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! In [[Romanian language|Romanian]] \n! In [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]]\n|-\n| B\u0103be\u0219ti\n| Kisb\u00e1bony\n|-\n| Dobol\u021b\n| Dabolc\n|-\n| Halmeu\n| Halmi\n|-\n| Halmeu-Vii\n| Halmihegy\n|-\n| Mesteac\u0103n\n| Ny\u00edrestanya\n|}\n\nUntil [[World War II]], the village was home to a Jewish community, which numbered 479 souls in 1877.<ref>[http://data.jewishgen.org/wconnect/wc.dll?jg~jgsys~shtetm~-1161123 JewishGen locality page for Halmeu]</ref> The commune included two other villages until 2005, when they were split off to form [[Porumbe\u0219ti, Satu Mare|Porumbe\u015fti]] Commune.\n\n==Demographics==\n\nIn 1910, 97.6% reported Hungarian as their primary language. The religious make-up was 1196 Calvinists (34.6%), 1061 Jewish (30.7%) and 613 Roman Catholic (17.7%).\n\nEthnic groups (2011 census):<ref>[http://www.recensamantromania.ro/rezultate-2/ Tab8. Popula\u0163ia stabil\u0103 dup\u0103 etnie \u2013 jude\u0163e, municipii, ora\u015fe, comune], 2011 census results, [[National Institute of Statistics (Romania)|Institutul Na\u021bional de Statistic\u0103]], accessed 10 March 2020.</ref> \n*[[Romanians]]: 57%\n*[[Hungarians in Romania|Hungarians]]: 36%\n*[[Romani people in Romania|Roma]]: 3%\n\n57% had [[Romanian language|Romanian]] as first language, and 39% [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]].<ref>[http://www.recensamantromania.ro/rezultate-2/ Tab10. Popula\u0163ia stabil\u0103 dup\u0103 limba matern\u0103 \u2013 jude\u0163e, municipii, ora\u015fe, comune], 2011 census results, [[National Institute of Statistics (Romania)|Institutul Na\u021bional de Statistic\u0103]], accessed 10 March 2020.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n* [http://simania.co.il/bookdetails.php?item_id=481430 Memorial book to the Communities of Halmin-Turt] (in Hebrew)\n\n{{LocalitiesSatuMare}}\n\n[[Category:Communes in Satu Mare County]]\n\n\n{{SatuMare-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Halmeu"}
